  "A quality inspector measures the diameter of 5 bolts (mm): 10.1, 10.0, 10.0, 9.9, 10.0. Calculate the population standard deviation.": "",
  "0.2 mm, which is considerably larger than the correct standard deviation": "",
  "0.1 mm, suggesting more variability in measurements than actually exists": "",
  "Approximately 0.063 mm": "",
  "0.01 mm, suggesting far less variability than the data actually show": "",
  "Mean = 50.0/5 = 10.0. Deviations: 0.1, 0, 0, −0.1, 0. SS = 0.01+0+0+0.01+0 = 0.02. Variance = 0.02/5 = 0.004. SD = √0.004 ≈ 0.063 mm.": "",
  "An investor tracks monthly returns (%) for two stocks over 6 months. Stock X: 2, 3, 2, 4, 3, 4. Stock Y: −5, 10, −3, 15, 1, 12. Both average 3% per month. Which stock is riskier, and why?": "",
